+## 8. Page-Specific Theme Switcher & Immersive Cinematic Reader Controls
+We have implemented custom, page-specific designs for the theme switchers and refactored the Cinematic Reader to run off of the main website theme system natively, cleaning up controls and adding a reading container width adjustment system.
+
+### 1. Customized Theme Switchers Per Page Layout
+- **[components/theme-switcher.tsx](file:///c:/Users/mande/Documents/Writer%20portfolio/components/theme-switcher.tsx)**:
+  - Added support for a `variant` prop (`"classic" | "aetheris" | "cinematic"`) to dynamically adapt the trigger button style and selection panel structure.
+  - **Classic**: Renders the standard easel icon button and a clean dropdown menu containing all 6 themes directly.
+  - **Aetheris**: Styled to match the glowing cyberpunk aesthetic. Renders the custom neon-cyan sun/moon combo icon inside a zinc-bordered button, and features a dark transparent dropdown menu (`bg-zinc-950/95 shadow-[0_0_25px_rgba(20,184,166,0.25)] border-zinc-800`) with monospace tracking uppercase fonts.
+  - **Cinematic**: Styled for the sci-fi reader HUD. Renders a minimalist circular moon/sun/palette icon button and opens an indigo-accented dropdown menu (`bg-[#05070a]/95 border-white/10 shadow-[0_0_30px_rgba(99,102,241,0.25)]`) positioned to align center-left of the HUD buttons on desktop, and upwards on mobile.
+- **[components/home-layouts/classic.tsx](file:///c:/Users/mande/Documents/Writer%20portfolio/components/home-layouts/classic.tsx)**: Passed `variant="classic"` to the header theme toggler.
+- **[components/home-layouts/aetheris.tsx](file:///c:/Users/mande/Documents/Writer%20portfolio/components/home-layouts/aetheris.tsx)**: Passed `variant="aetheris"` to the telemetry-bar theme switchers.
+
+### 2. Website Theme Integration in Cinematic Reader
+- **[components/reader-layouts/cinematic.tsx](file:///c:/Users/mande/Documents/Writer%20portfolio/components/reader-layouts/cinematic.tsx)**:
+  - Imported `useTheme` from `theme-provider` and mapped global themes directly. Removed the separate local `settings.theme` state.
+  - mapped themes dynamically: `lm-theme-light` applies the light background, `lm-theme-sunset` applies the cozy sepia/sunset palette, and all other dark/colored themes (`dark`, `grey`, `purple`, `forest`) apply the immersive dark interface with glowing particles.
+  - Replaced all header, locks, buttons, and container styling checks with `isDarkTheme`, `isSepiaTheme` and `isLightTheme` flags.
+
+### 3. Display Settings Adjustments
+- **Style Presets**:
+  - Removed `theme` field from predefined presets. Presets now apply typography, glow, and drop cap presets without overriding the active website theme.
+- **Content Box Width Slider**:
