+## 9. Nested Comment Reply System & Redesigned Reader Comments Layouts
+We have implemented a nested two-layer comment reply system (parent comments and child replies) across the platform.
+
+### 1. Database Schema Updates
+- **[schema.prisma](file:///c:/Users/mande/Documents/Writer%20portfolio/prisma/schema.prisma)**:
+  - Added the self-referential `parentId` relation with cascade deletions to the `Comment` model:
+    ```prisma
+    parentId  String?
+    parent    Comment?  @relation("CommentReplies", fields: [parentId], references: [id], onDelete: Cascade)
+    replies   Comment[] @relation("CommentReplies")
+    ```
+  - Added an index on `parentId` for optimized query performance.
+  - Resolved database migration drift (where `Story.scheduledAt` was not in previous migrations) and successfully ran `npx prisma migrate dev --name add_comment_replies` to generate and apply the database updates.
+
+### 2. Comments API Nesting & Flattening
+- **[route.ts](file:///c:/Users/mande/Documents/Writer%20portfolio/app/api/comments/route.ts)**:
+  - Extended Zod validation schema to accept `parentId` in the request body.
+  - Modified the `GET` route to only return top-level comments (where `parentId: null`), including child `replies` ordered chronologically (`createdAt: "asc"`) along with user metadata.
+  - Updated the `POST` route to resolve and flatten replies: if a user replies to a comment that is already a reply, the system automatically sets the new comment's `parentId` to the top-level parent ID to enforce a clean, flat two-layer comment hierarchy.
+
+### 3. Redesigned Classic Comments Section
+- **[classic.tsx](file:///c:/Users/mande/Documents/Writer%20portfolio/components/reader-layouts/classic.tsx)**:
+  - Redesigned comment cards with nested reply threads.
+  - Added a collapsible, user-friendly inline reply form that expands directly under each parent comment card.
+  - Styled replies with indented left-border connector lines, smaller avatars, and a dedicated response workflow.
+
+### 4. Redesigned Cinematic Comments Sanctuary
+- **[cinematic.tsx](file:///c:/Users/mande/Documents/Writer%20portfolio/components/reader-layouts/cinematic.tsx)**:
+  - Redesigned comment cards to fit the cyberpunk sci-fi console aesthetic.
+  - Added circular node indicators and a minimalist hud-themed `[ Reply ]` text link button.
+  - Integrated a sleek, dark inline transmission box with dynamic animation triggers (`animate-in fade-in`).
+  - Rendered nested replies inside dark translucent background boxes (`bg-slate-950/40`) with left borders and customized sub-avatar badges.
 

