diff --git a/components/reader-layouts/cinematic.tsx b/components/reader-layouts/cinematic.tsx
--- a/components/reader-layouts/cinematic.tsx
+++ b/components/reader-layouts/cinematic.tsx
@@ -134,4 +134,32 @@
   - Added circular node indicators and a minimalist hud-themed `[ Reply ]` text link button.
   - Integrated a sleek, dark inline transmission box with dynamic animation triggers (`animate-in fade-in`).
   - Rendered nested replies inside dark translucent background boxes (`bg-slate-950/40`) with left borders and customized sub-avatar badges.
+
+---
+
+## 10. Comment Liking, Single Input Box Reply Flow & Viewport-Floating Controls
+We have implemented comment/reply liking, added chapter-level like counts, restricted comment modifications to authors/admins, routed all reply creations through the main comment input box, and designed the main input container to float dynamically at the viewport bottom in reply mode with auto-expanding height.
+
+### 1. Chapter and Comment Liking with Counts
+- **[classic.tsx](file:///c:/Users/mande/Documents/Writer%20portfolio/components/reader-layouts/classic.tsx)** & **[cinematic.tsx](file:///c:/Users/mande/Documents/Writer%20portfolio/components/reader-layouts/cinematic.tsx)**:
+  - Added `chapterLikesCount` state, populated on mount/chapter change from the `/api/ratings` endpoint.
+  - Updated the chapter Like/Heart button to show the count next to the button text: `Like ({chapterLikesCount})`.
+  - Added a `handleLikeComment` function which optimistically updates the comments tree state and triggers a `POST` or `DELETE` request to `/api/comments/[commentId]/like`.
+  - Added Heart/ThumbsUp icon buttons under both parent comments and child replies to show and toggle likes.
+
+### 2. Permission-Based Comment Control Dropdowns
+- **[classic.tsx](file:///c:/Users/mande/Documents/Writer%20portfolio/components/reader-layouts/classic.tsx)** & **[cinematic.tsx](file:///c:/Users/mande/Documents/Writer%20portfolio/components/reader-layouts/cinematic.tsx)**:
+  - Hides the three-dots edit/delete dropdown menu entirely if the comment or reply was written by another user and the current user is not an admin.
+  - Ensures standard users only see the menu on their own comments, while admins retain delete rights globally.
+
+### 3. Unified Reply Input Box Flow
+- Rerouted all comments and replies to share the main comment input box.
+- Clicking "Reply" sets the active parent comment ID (`activeReplyId`) and registers the target author's name (`replyToUser`), focusing and shifting the main input box.
+- Displays a dedicated "Replying to @username [X]" banner in the main input box to easily cancel and return to general comment mode.
